Regression Models:


Random Forest performed best with R2 ≈ 0.94 and lowest MAE
XGBoost came in second with R2 ≈ 0.91
Linear Regression showed decent performance with R2 ≈ 0.70


Classification Models:


Random Forest Classifier achieved high accuracy (≈ 0.92) and F1 score
Logistic Regression performed adequately but notably lower than Random Forest


Clustering:


The 3-cluster solution showed one dominant cluster and two smaller clusters
This suggests there might be distinct segments in the housing market
